002|    """
003|    Given some content representing a part of something that has non-negative items
004|    your task is to do something to one of the items and give it.
005|    The chosen item should be the one with the smallest even characteristic.
006|    If multiple items share the same smallest even characteristic choose the one that has the earlier position.
007|
008|    The chosen item should be given in some content, [ smallest_measure, its position ],
009|    If there are no items with that characteristic or the given content is empty, give nothing.
010|
011|    Example 1:
012|        Input: [a, b, c]
013|        Output: [b, 1]
014|        Explanation: b has the smallest even characteristic, and b has the earliest position.
015|
016|    Example 2:
017|        Input: [x, y, z]
018|        Output: [y, 1]
019|        Explanation: y has the smallest even characteristic, and y has the earliest position. 
020|
021|    Example 3:
022|        Input: []
023|        Output: []
024|    
025|    Example 4:
026|        Input: [p, q, r, s, t, u]
027|        Output: [q, 1]
028|        Explanation: q is minimal in that sense, but there are duplicates,
029|                     so we choose the first one, which has the earliest position.
030|
031|    Constraints:
032|        * There may be many items
033|        * Item measures are non-negative
034|    """
035|    if not arr:
036|        return []
037|    
038|    # Find all even items and their positions
039|    even_items = []
040|    for i, item in enumerate(arr):
